nhgis_ext <-  define_extract_nhgis(description = "CW8: Persons by Sex by Race at county level", time_series_tables = tst_spec("CW8",geog_levels =c("county"),years = c("2010","2000")
                                                                                                                              )
                                   )

nhgis_ext_submitted <- submit_extract(nhgis_ext)

nhgis_ext_complete <- wait_for_extract(nhgis_ext_submitted)

filepath1 <- download_extract(nhgis_ext_submitted,download_dir = "C:/Users/aubin/OneDrive - Aix-Marseille Université/AIX EN PROVENCE/MASTER 1 ECONOMETRIE STATISTIQUE/S2/Data_Visualisation/PROJET_1/data")

pop <- read_csv(filepath1)

# clean up the table (‘pop’ -> ‘pop1’) and create columns for the different populations

pop1 <- pop %>% 
  mutate(STATEA = as.integer(STATEA)) %>% 
  filter(!(STATEA %in% c(2,15))) %>% 
  mutate(
    pop_white = CW8AA2010 + CW8AG2010,
    pop_black = CW8AB2010 + CW8AH2010,
    pop_native = CW8AC2010 + CW8AI2010,
    pop_asian = CW8AD2010 + CW8AJ2010,
    pop_other = CW8AE2010 + CW8AK2010,
    pop_two_more_other_race = CW8AF2010 + CW8AL2010
        ) %>% 
  select(
    pop_white, pop_black, pop_native, pop_asian , pop_other, pop_two_more_other_race, GISJOIN, GEOGYEAR
        ) %>% 
  mutate(
    pop_total = pop_white + pop_black + pop_asian + pop_native + pop_other + pop_two_more_other_race
        )

pop1

# Joining two datasets

shape_us <- left_join(shape_us, pop1, by = c("GISJOIN" = "GISJOIN"))

shape_us

2 : County population bar plot

Task 1

library(sf)
library(RColorBrewer)

# Creation of a dataset to manage data on the city of Los Angeles

data_los_angeles <- shape_us %>% 
  filter(GEOID == '06037') %>% 
  select(pop_white,pop_black,pop_native,pop_native,pop_asian,pop_other,pop_total) %>%
  st_drop_geometry()

# Reorganisation of the ‘data_los_angeles’ dataframe

data_los_angeles <- data_los_angeles %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols=c(pop_white, 
                      pop_black, 
                      pop_asian, 
                      pop_native, 
                      pop_other
                      ),
               names_to = 'race',
               values_to='nombre_population') %>%
  arrange(nombre_population)


# Start creating the graphic 

# Creation of a colour palette based on the different breeds
palette_colors <- brewer.pal(n = length(unique(data_los_angeles$race)), name = "Reds")

# customising labels
labels_perso <- c(
  "pop_white" = "Whites",
  "pop_black" = "Blacks",
  "pop_asian" = "Asians",
  "pop_native" = "Indians",
  "pop_other" = "Others"
)

# application of custom labels 
data_los_angeles <- data_los_angeles %>% 
  mutate(race_label = labels_perso[race])

# rank populations in ascending order and adjust text in bars
data_los_angeles <- data_los_angeles %>%
  mutate(rank_pop = rank(
    nombre_population, 
    ties.method = "first"
                        ),
         text_position = ifelse(rank_pop <= 3, 
                                nombre_population + 5000, 
                                nombre_population / 10
                                ),# adjustment of text position
         text_color = ifelse(rank_pop <= 3,
                             "black",
                             "white"
                             ), # adjust text colour 
         text_hjust = ifelse(rank_pop <= 3,
                             -0.7, 
                             0.01)
      )  # text alignment



# Graph raw data

plt_LA <- ggplot(data_los_angeles,
                 aes(x = nombre_population,
                     y = fct_reorder(race_label, 
                                     nombre_population
                                     ),
                     fill = race)
                 ) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = palette_colors) +
  geom_text(aes(x = text_position, 
                y = race_label, 
                label = race_label, 
                color = text_color),
            hjust = data_los_angeles$text_hjust,
            size = 4) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    legend.position = 'none',
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "County: Los Angeles",
    x = "population",
    y = "race"
  )

print(plt_LA)


# Graph showing the share of the various populations in the county's total population

data_los_angeles <- data_los_angeles %>% 
  mutate(
    part_pop = nombre_population / pop_total
        )

margins <- unit(c(1.5, 1, 1, 1), "cm")

plt_part_pop_LA <- ggplot(data_los_angeles, 
                          aes(x = part_pop, 
                              y = fct_reorder(race_label, 
                                              part_pop
                                              ),

                          ) +
  geom_col() +

  theme_minimal() +

    panel.background = element_blank(),
    legend.position = 'none',
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),

4 : Leaflet

Task 3

library(leaflet)

# Creating the interactive map

shape_us <- st_transform(shape_us, 4326)

pal_fun <- colorQuantile("YlOrRd", NULL, n=8)

col1 <- RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(n=8, name='OrRd')

n_classes <- 8

bks <- classInt::classIntervals(c(min(shape_us$pop_total) - .00001,
                                  shape_us$pop_total),
                                n=n_classes, style = "quantile")$brks


p_popup <- paste0(
  "<strong>Total Population: </strong>", format(shape_us$pop_total, big.mark = ","), "<br>",
  "<strong>County ID: </strong>", shape_us$GEOID, "<br>",
  "<strong>County: </strong>", shape_us$NAME, "<br>",
  "<strong>State: </strong>", shape_us$STATE
)


us_pop <-leaflet(shape_us) %>%
  addPolygons(
    stroke = TRUE, color="black", 
    opacity=.2,weight=2,popup = p_popup,
    fillColor = ~pal_fun(pop_total),
    fillOpacity = 1, smoothFactor = 0.5,
    group = "county"
            ) %>% 
  addTiles(group = 'OSM'
           ) %>% 
  addLegend('bottomright',
            colors = col1,
            labels = paste0("up to ",
                            format(bks[-1],
                                   digits = 2)
                            ),
            title ="Population des USA par comté"
            ) %>%
  addLayersControl(baseGroups = c("OSM"), 
                   overlayGroups = c("county")
                   )

us_pop

5 : Shiny

Task 4

library(shiny)

# Dashboard creation

# small adjustments

sum(is.na(shape_us$pop_total))
shape_us_clean <- shape_us %>% filter(!is.na(pop_total))
shape_us <- shape_us %>%
  left_join(pop %>% select(GISJOIN, STATE), by = "GISJOIN")

# Shiny:

ui <- fluidPage(
  titlePanel("US County Population in 2010"),
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      uiOutput("select_state"),
      uiOutput("counties_in_state")
    ),   
    mainPanel(
      leafletOutput("map", width = "80%", height = "500px"), 
      textOutput("text"),
      plotOutput("BarPlot", width = "80%", height = "500px")
    )
  )
)

server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  # Dynamic state selection
  output$select_state <- renderUI({
    selectInput(
      "select_state",
      "State:",
      choices = unique(shape_us$STATE),
      selected = unique(shape_us$STATE)[1]
    )
  })
  
  # Dynamic county selection
  output$counties_in_state <- renderUI({
    req(input$select_state)  # verification
    selectInput(
      "select_county",
      "County:",
      choices = shape_us$NAME[shape_us$STATE == input$select_state]
    )
  })
  
  # Population graph by breed
  output$BarPlot <- renderPlot({
    req(input$select_county)  # verification
    
    # redefinition of ‘shape_us’ to display interactive bar plots
    temp <- shape_us %>%
      filter(NAME == input$select_county) %>% 
      select(pop_white, pop_black, pop_native, pop_asian, pop_other, pop_total) %>% 
      st_drop_geometry() %>% 
      pivot_longer(cols=c(pop_white, pop_black, pop_native, pop_asian, pop_other),
                   names_to = 'race',
                   values_to = 'nombre_population') %>% 
      arrange(nombre_population)
    
    req(nrow(temp)>0) # verification
    labels_perso <- c(
      "pop_white" = "Whites",
      "pop_black" = "Blacks",
      "pop_asian" = "Asians",
      "pop_native" = "Indians",
      "pop_other" = "Others"
    )
    
    temp <- temp %>%
      mutate(race_label = labels_perso[race])
    
    p1 <- ggplot(temp, 
                 aes(x = nombre_population, 
                           y = fct_reorder(race_label, nombre_population), 
                           fill = race
                           )
                 ) +
      geom_col() +
      scale_fill_manual(values = palette_colors) +
      geom_text(aes(label = race_label,
                    x = max(nombre_population)*0.5
                    ), 
                color = "black",
                size = 5,
                nudge_x = -2
                ) +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        legend.position = 'none',
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
        plot.margin = margins
      ) +
      labs(
        title = paste0("County: ", input$select_county),
        x = "Population",
        y = "Race"
      )
    
    temp <- temp %>% 
      mutate(part_pop = nombre_population/pop_total)
    
    margins <- unit(c(2.2, 1, 1, 1), "cm")
    
    p2 <- ggplot(temp, 
                 aes(x = part_pop,
                     y = fct_reorder(race_label, part_pop),
                     fill = race_label)
                 ) +
      geom_col() +
      scale_fill_manual(values = palette_colors) +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        legend.position = 'none',
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
        plot.margin = margins
      ) +
      labs(y = "", x = "Population Share")
    
    grid.arrange(p1, p2, nrow = 1)
  })
  
  output$map <- renderLeaflet({
    req(shape_us$pop_total)  # verification
    
    pal_fun <- colorQuantile("YlOrRd", domain = shape_us$pop_total, n = 8)
    col1 <- RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(n = 8, name = 'YlOrRd')
    
    bks <- classInt::classIntervals(c(min(shape_us_clean$pop_total) - 1e-05, shape_us_clean$pop_total),n = 8, style = "quantile")$brks
    
    # Popup content to display county details
    p_popup <- paste0(
      "<strong>Total Population: </strong>", format(shape_us$pop_total, big.mark = ","), "<br>",
      "<strong>County ID: </strong>", shape_us$GEOID, "<br>",
      "<strong>County: </strong>", shape_us$NAME, "<br>",
      "<strong>State: </strong>", shape_us$STATE
    )
    
    
    leaflet(shape_us) %>%
      addPolygons(
        stroke = TRUE, color = "black", opacity = .2, weight = 2,
        fillColor = ~pal_fun(pop_total),
        fillOpacity = 1, smoothFactor = 0.5,
        popup = p_popup,
        group = "county") %>% 
      addTiles(group = 'OSM') %>% 
      addLegend('bottomright',
                colors = col1,
                labels = paste0("Up to ", format(bks[-1], digits = 2)),
                title = "Total Population") %>%
      addLayersControl(baseGroups = c("OSM"), 
                       overlayGroups = c("county"))
  })
  
  # selected counties updated by clicking on the map
  observeEvent(input$map_shape_click, {
    req(input$map_shape_click$id)
    
    output$text <- renderText({
      paste0("County ID: ", input$map_shape_click$id)
    })
    
    updateSelectInput(session, "select_county",
                      choices = shape_us$NAME[shape_us$GEOID == input$map_shape_click$id])
  })
}

# launch the Shiny application
shinyApp(ui, server)
